lead_paragraph: Even as voters rage and candidates put up ads against government bailouts, the reviled mother of them all -- the $700 billion lifeline to banks, insurance and auto companies -- will expire after Sunday at a fraction of that cost, and could conceivably earn taxpayers a profit, Jackie Calmes writes in The New York Times.
